<subSubSection lastPageId="53" lastPageNumber="54" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="51.[151,1437,2006,2031]" box="[151,1437,2006,2031]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,2006,2031]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Diagnosis</emphasis>
: Dorsal fur color brownish grizzled with black, ventral color pure white, line of demarcation distinct.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="52.[151,1437,151,320]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">
White patches above eye and behind ear. Ears with pigmentation (
<figureCitation box="[893,1007,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURE 59" captionStartId="52.[151,250,1098,1120]" captionTargetBox="[264,1323,373,1076]" captionTargetId="figure@52.[264,1323,373,1076]" captionTargetPageId="52" captionText="FIGURE 59. Tristram's jird, Meriones tristrami from Gharandal (Photo by Mohammad Abu Baker)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202893/files/figure.png" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Figure 59</figureCitation>
). Sole partially covered with hair. Tail longer than head body length with a small black brush. Claws pale in color. Four pairs of mammae. Skull small with small tympanic bullae, the posterior part of the bullae does not extend beyond the paraoccipital. Braincase rounded at posterior end. Suprameatal triangle of bullae completely closed. Upper incisors with anterior median groove (
<figureCitation box="[243,357,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURE 60" captionStartId="52.[151,250,2006,2028]" captionTargetBox="[340,1247,1169,1984]" captionTargetId="figure@52.[340,1247,1169,1984]" captionTargetPageId="52" captionText="FIGURE 60.A. Dorsal,B. Ventral, C. Lateral views of the skull, and D. Upper maxillary cheeckteeth for Meriones tristrami." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202895/files/figure.png" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Figure 60</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
